flSPuv0.sdn_parameter_name: Fluorescence of the water body by linear-response CDOM fluorometer
flSPuv0.definition: This code is under review due to its ambiguity. It is likely to be deprecated at the end of the review period. Please use terms stating 'Concentration of%' for calibrated CDOM fluorometer output or 'Raw signal% of%' for the raw fluorescence signal [updated 30/07/2019]. Definition was: The amount of violet to low ultra-violet radiation generated in the water column in response to high ultra-violet radiation transmission expressed relative to an unspecified baseline using fluorometer designed to detect CDOM, crude oil or UV-fluorescent dyes.

timeS.comments: Elapsed time (seconds) based on first scan in data file and sample rate (profiling) or sample interval (moorings); sample rate is defined by configuration (.con or .xmlcon) file.

timeM.comments: Elapsed time (minutes) based on first scan in data file and sample rate (profiling) or sample interval (moorings); sample rate or interval is as defined by configuration (.con or .xmlcon) file.

timeH.comments: Elapsed time (hours) based on first scan in data file and sample rate (profiling) or sample interval (moorings); sample rate or interval is as defined by configuration (.con or .xmlcon) file.

timeJ.comments: Elapsed time (Julian days) based on first scan in data file and sample rate (profiling) or sample interval (moorings); sample rate or interval is as defined by configuration (.con or .xmlcon) file.

timeN.comments: From NMEA device: Seconds since January 1, 1970; only for SBE 45

timeQ.comments: From NMEA device: Seconds since January 1, 2000; everything but SBE 45

timeK.comments: Seconds since January 1, 2000, based on time stamp in 16plus V2 or 19plus V2 (in moored mode).

timeJV2.comments: Julian days, based on time stamp in 16plus V2 or 19plus V2 (in moored mode).

timeSCP.comments: Julian days, based on time stamp in 16plus or 19plus (in moored mode). Not applicable to V2 versions.

timeY.comments: Computer time (seconds) since January 1, 1970, appended by Seasave V7 if 'Scan time added' selected in configuration (.con or .xmlcon) file.
